quest\nurls=[\n 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sksamuel/hoplite/master/README.md',\n 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sksamuel/hoplite/v3.0.0.RC1/README.md',\n]\nfor u in urls:\n  try:\n    data=urllib.request.urlopen(u, timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8', 'replace')\n    print('URL',u,'len',len(data))\n    for term in ['Installation','Usage','HOCON','YAML','hoplite-core','dependency']:\n      i=data.lower().find(term.lower())\n      if i!=-1:\n        print('---',term,'---')\n        print(data[max(0,i-400):i+800])\n  except Exception as e: print('ERR',u,e)\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1857, "output": 320, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34433, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782710348427, "responseId": "resp_03c736f65ca33551016a42004d05b48190be621f7cccb849b2"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fud5ovDwAsLX9UuKqBfmroPs|fc_03c736f65ca33551016a42004fb5f481909363b8702c97c845", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "URL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sksamuel/hoplite/master/README.md len 62084\n--- Usage ---\n                                         |\n| `SecretFilesPreprocessor`      | Replaces any strings of the form `${secret:key}` with the contents of the file at `<basePath>/<key>`. Useful for Kubernetes / Docker deployments where each secret is mounted as a separate file inside a directory. Not registered automatically — see the [SecretFilesPreprocessor](#secretfilespreprocessor) section below for usage.                                                                                                  |\n\n\n\n\n### Optional Preprocessors\n\nThese preprocessors must be added to the `ConfigBuilder` before they take effect, and require extra modules to be added to the build.\n\n| Preprocessor                    | Function                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |\n|:--------------------------------|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n--- HOCON ---\nF%2Fcentral.sonatype.com%2Frepository%2Fmaven-snapshots%2Fcom%2Fsksamuel%2Fhoplite%2Fhoplite-core%2Fmaven-metadata.xml&strategy=highestVersion&label=maven-snapshot\">](https://central.sonatype.com/repository/maven-snapshots/com/sksamuel/hoplite/hoplite-core/maven-metadata.xml)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multiple formats:** Write your configuration in [several formats](#supported-formats): Yaml, JSON, Toml, Hocon, or\n  Java .props files or even mix and match formats in the same system.\n- **Property Sources:** Per-system overrides are possible from JVM system properties,\n  environment variables, JNDI or a per-user local config file.\n- **Batteries included:** Support for many [standard types](#decoders) such as primitives, enums, dates, collection\n  types, inline classes, uuids, nullable types, as well as popular Kotlin third party library types such\n  as `NonEmptyList`, `Option` and `TupleX` from [Arrow](https://arrow-kt.io/).\n- **Custom Data Types:** The `Decoder` interface makes it easy to add support for your custom domain types or standard\n  library types not covered out of the box.\n- **Cascading:** Config files can be [stacked](#cascading-config). Start with a default file and then layer \n--- YAML ---\ndataUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fcentral.sonatype.com%2Frepository%2Fmaven-snapshots%2Fcom%2Fsksamuel%2Fhoplite%2Fhoplite-core%2Fmaven-metadata.xml&strategy=highestVersion&label=maven-snapshot\">](https://central.sonatype.com/repository/maven-snapshots/com/sksamuel/hoplite/hoplite-core/maven-metadata.xml)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multiple formats:** Write your configuration in [several formats](#supported-formats): Yaml, JSON, Toml, Hocon, or\n  Java .props files or even mix and match formats in the same system.\n- **Property Sources:** Per-system overrides are possible from JVM system properties,\n  environment variables, JNDI or a per-user local config file.\n- **Batteries included:** Support for many [standard types](#decoders) such as primitives, enums, dates, collection\n  types, inline classes, uuids, nullable types, as well as popular Kotlin third party library types such\n  as `NonEmptyList`, `Option` and `TupleX` from [Arrow](https://arrow-kt.io/).\n- **Custom Data Types:** The `Decoder` interface makes it easy to add support for your custom domain types or standard\n  library types not covered out of the box.\n- **Cascading:** Config files can be [stacked](#cascading-config). Start with a default fi\n--- hoplite-core ---\ntartup Hoplite will read from one or more config files,\nmapping the values in those files into your config classes. Any missing values, or values that cannot be converted\ninto the required type will cause the config to fail with detailed error messages.\n\n![master](https://github.com/sksamuel/hoplite/workflows/master/badge.svg)\n[<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/maven-central/v/com.sksamuel.hoplite/hoplite-core.svg?label=latest%20release\"/>](http://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Choplite)\n[<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/maven-metadata/v?metadataUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fcentral.sonatype.com%2Frepository%2Fmaven-snapshots%2Fcom%2Fsksamuel%2Fhoplite%2Fhoplite-core%2Fmaven-metadata.xml&strategy=highestVersion&label=maven-snapshot\">](https://central.sonatype.com/repository/maven-snapshots/com/sksamuel/hoplite/hoplite-core/maven-metadata.xml)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multiple formats:** Write your configuration in [several formats](#supported-formats): Yaml, JSON, Toml, Hocon, or\n  Java .props files or even mix and match f